      "body": {
        "type": "TextualBody",
        "value": "The first instance of reflection that the audience is introduced to is not through a mirror, but through the bread knife. When in the bread loaf, it reflects the tablecloth, but when it falls--of its own accord--it reflects the bread itself. The camera lingers on this shot, likely to highlight the importance of this (the knife) particular piece of mise-en-scene",
        "format": "text/plain",
        "purpose": "commenting"
      },
      "target": {
        "source": {
